article.headline: Johnson's 16 points led the way
article.linkText: Liberty stop Rockers, halt franchise-worst skid
article.story:
NEW YORK (AP) -- Breaking a franchise-high losing streak was a start, but the New York Liberty won't feel good until they lock up a playoff spot. Vickie Johnson scored 16 points and the Liberty snapped a five-game losing streak with a 60-48 win over the Cleveland Rockers on Sunday. "I would say it's a big win -- it's a win, and we haven't had one of those in a while," center Tari Phillips said. "After losing five in a row, every game is a must win. We must win just to feel better. "And this feels better, Ill tell you that." Phillips had 12 points and 11 rebounds to notch her eighth double-double for the Liberty (10-13), who shot 46 percent from the field and were never threatened by Cleveland's ineffective offense. New York, which lost to Detroit on a last-second shot Friday, is fighting for the fourth playoff spot in the Eastern Conference. "Its still very close -- no one can afford to go into a drought right now," coach Richie Adubato said. Chasity Melvin scored 18 points and LaToya Thomas added 14 for Cleveland (12-14), which shot 33 percent from the field and hit only one of its 13 3-point attempts. Reserves Linda Frohlich and Elena Baranova made layups and Johnson sank a 3-pointer with Deanna Jackson in her face to push New York's lead to 46-29 with 7:55 left in the game. The Liberty limited the Rockers to only three baskets in the first 12 minutes of the second half. "They are much better when they can play off of their defense," Cleveland coach Dan Hughes said. "We didn't do a very good job of pressuring the ball. They made it tough on us, but we missing some opportunities, too." Melvin scored 16 points down the stretch to cut the lead to 10 points. Cleveland pressed New York in the final four minutes but couldn't complete the comeback. The Rockers' poor shooting helped the Liberty build a double-digit lead in the first half. Cleveland went 6:21 without scoring as the Liberty went on a 13-0 run and took a 33-23 lead into halftime. "That was a heartbreaking loss," Crystal Robinson said of Fridays defeat. "We have to use this momentum now. Every game is a must-win if we want to get in the playoffs." New York got 21 points from its bench, including eight from Elena Baranova and six from Erin Thorn, who scored a career high 12 against Detroit on Friday. "A couple of my veterans look tired right now, today," Adubato said. "It's a matter of resting people so they can play down the stretch."

Game notes
Liberty F Tamika Whitmore returned to the starting lineup after coming off the bench for four games. ... Cleveland G Merlakia Jones left the game 4:42 before halftime after bruising her right hand in a collision with Frohlich, but returned for the second half. ... New York backup PG K.B. Sharp didn't play for the second consecutive game after spraining her right ankle Tuesday.
